quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,187,"They ask you, [O Muḥammad], about the Hour: when is its arrival?{1} Say, ",1:[Literally, "resting" or "establishment."],2:[i.e., it is a source of concern, worry or fear.]
  7,188,"Say, "
  7,189,"It is He who created you from one soul and created from it its mate that he{1} might dwell in security with her. And when he [i.e., man] covers her,{2} she carries a light burden [i.e., a pregnancy] and continues therein. And when it becomes heavy, they both invoke Allāh, their Lord, ",1:[i.e., man or every descendent of Adam.],2:[An allusion to sexual intercourse.],3:[Physically sound or righteous.]
  9,91,"There is not upon the weak or upon the ill or upon those who do not find anything to spend any discomfort [i.e., guilt] when they are sincere to Allāh and His Messenger. There is not upon the doers of good any cause [for blame]. And Allāh is Forgiving and Merciful."
  9,92,"Nor [is there blame] upon those who, when they came to you for you to take them along, you said, ",1:[No mounts or even shoes were available.]
  9,93,"The cause [for blame] is only upon those who ask permission of you while they are rich. They are satisfied to be with those who stay behind, and Allāh has sealed over their hearts, so they do not know."
  10,49,"Say, "
  10,50,"Say, ",1:["Impatience" refers to the disbelievers' ridicule of the Prophet (ﷺ) by telling him to produce Allāh's punishment as proof of his truthfulness.]
  10,51,"Then is it that when it has [actually] occurred you will believe in it? Now?{1} And you were [once] for it impatient.{2}",1:[i.e., when it is too late to benefit from belief.],2:[Challenging those who warned of it to bring it on immediately.]
  11,16,"Those are the ones for whom there is not in the Hereafter but the Fire. And lost is what they did therein,{1} and worthless is what they used to do.",1:[i.e., during worldly life.]
  11,17,"So is one who [stands] upon a clear evidence from his Lord [like the aforementioned]? And a witness{1} from Him follows it,{2} and before it was the Scripture of Moses to lead and as mercy. Those [believers in the former revelations] believe in it [i.e., the Qur’ān]. But whoever disbelieves in it from the [various] factions - the Fire is his promised destination. So be not in doubt about it. Indeed, it is the truth from your Lord, but most of the people do not believe.",1:[Referring to Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ)],2:[or to the angel Gabriel.]
  11,18,"And who is more unjust than he who invents a lie about Allāh? Those will be presented before their Lord, and the witnesses will say, "
